# =============================================================================
# BNI PALMS Analytics - Frontend Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# Never commit the .env file to version control!
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # Edit .env with your actual values
#   npm start
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL - Backend API base URL
# The frontend will make API requests to this URL
#
# Development (local backend):
#   REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8000
#
# Production examples:
#   REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
#   REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=https://your-backend.vercel.app
#
# Default: http://localhost:8000
REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# React Environment Variables:
# - Must start with REACT_APP_ to be accessible in the app
# - Changes require restarting the development server (npm start)
# - Values are embedded at BUILD TIME (not runtime)
# - For production builds, set these in your hosting platform
#
# Build-time vs Runtime:
# ✅ Build time: Environment variables are embedded in the JavaScript bundle
# ❌ Runtime: Cannot change after the app is built
#
# Production Deployment:
# - Vercel: Set in Project Settings > Environment Variables
# - Netlify: Set in Site Settings > Build & Deploy > Environment
# - Other: Consult your hosting provider's documentation
#
# =============================================================================
# Production Checklist
# =============================================================================
# Before deploying to production, ensure:
#
# ✅ REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL points to your production backend
# ✅ Backend URL uses HTTPS (not HTTP)
# ✅ Backend CORS is configured to allow your frontend domain
# ✅ Environment variables are set in hosting platform
# ✅ Build is triggered after changing environment variables
# =============================================================================
